    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD3S, representing the pinnacle of Japanese front-midship engineering. This specimen features the iconic 13B-REW rotary engine, utilizing a sequential twin-turbocharger configuration that provides seamless boost transition across the RPM range. The drivetrain is paired with a precise five-speed manual transmission and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis remains a masterclass in balance, utilizing a four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a lightweight aluminum-intensive frame to achieve a perfect 50:50 weight distribution. This vehicle is in concours condition; the paint depth is consistent across all panels, and the interior retains its original textures with no UV damage to the dash or bolster wear on the seats. Recent preventative maintenance includes a full cooling system refresh with an aluminum multi-core radiator and a comprehensive compression test confirming optimal health across all rotor faces. A rare, unmodified survivor for the discerning enthusiast.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
