      "description": "This 996-generation Carrera 4S represents a pinnacle of analog driver engagement. Featuring the iconic wide-body silhouette and integrated rear reflector strip, this specimen is mechanically impeccable. The 3.6L flat-six delivers linear power through a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle and an all-wheel-drive system with a viscous coupling for optimal torque distribution. This example boasts a documented IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement, ensuring long-term reliability. The suspension retains its factory-spec damping rates, and the chassis remains remarkably stiff. Finished in a concours-ready coat with an interior devoid of bolster wear or plastic degradation, this is a turn-key investment for the discerning purist.",
